  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nAnalogous to the validator client option `--beacon-node-api-endpoint`, introduce `--beacon-node-api-endpoints` that takes a comma-separated list of one or more consensus client REST API endpoints. Eventually, deprecate `--beacon-node-api-endpoint`.\r\n\r\n### Rationale\r\n\r\nThis helps with setups that use a single validator client pointed at multiple consensus clients in the backend. For example, I am running a Lighthouse validator client that fails over between Lighthouse, Teku and Nimbus. It'd be great to have more choices for the validator client.\r\n",
