    "body": "In case of consensus client failure or maintenance, yes. For example, the EL may need to be pruned or resynced. This would, I presume, mean the CL can no longer sync until that's completed (post-merge). Another example, the host OS gets patched and the server reboots.\r\n\r\nI see maintenance events once or twice a month, and the Lighthouse VC I currently use just fails over to another CL when they happen.\r\n",
